{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 18:56:25.543680", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nOverview\n- Environment: Hierarchical enterprise network with FRR OSPF, server farm at 10.200.0.0/24 hosting DNS (10.200.0.2), Apache web servers (web0.local…web3.local at 10.200.0.3–10.200.0.6), and Nginx load balancer (web99.local at 10.200.0.7).\n- Access hosts examined: host_1_1_1_1 (10.1.1.11 via 10.1.1.1) and host_2_1_1_1 (10.2.1.13 via 10.2.1.1).\n\nKey Tests and Evidence\n1) Layer-3 reachability\n- Global ping matrix shows 0% loss and low RTTs among hosts and server farm components (including DNS, LB, web servers), indicating OSPF routing and underlay are healthy.\n- Specific pings:\n  - host_2_1_1_1 → 10.200.0.7 (LB): 0% loss, avg ~2.84 ms\n  - host_2_1_1_1 → 10.200.0.3 (web0): 0% loss, avg ~3.22 ms\n  - host_2_1_1_1 → 10.200.0.2 (DNS): 0% loss, avg ~3.18 ms\n- Traceroute host_2_1_1_1 → 10.200.0.3 traverses expected path and completes in ~7.7 ms.\n\n2) Host IP config and routing\n- host_1_1_1_1: 10.1.1.11/24, default via 10.1.1.1\n- host_2_1_1_1: 10.2.1.13/24, default via 10.2.1.1\n- Both appear dynamically configured and correct for their subnets.\n\n3) DNS resolution\n- Both hosts use DNS server 10.200.0.2 (/etc/resolv.conf) and resolve:\n  - web0.local → 10.200.0.3, web1.local → .4, web2.local → .5, web3.local → .6, web99.local → .7\n\n4) Application-layer HTTP tests (curl)\n- host_1_1_1_1:\n  - HTTP to web99.local and 10.200.0.7: successful; connect ~3–10 ms, TTFB ~0.19–0.38 s, total ~1.0–1.2 s\n  - HTTP to web0.local and 10.200.0.3: successful; similar timings, ~1.0–1.13 s total\n- host_2_1_1_1:\n  - HTTP to web99.local, web0.local, 10.200.0.7, 10.200.0.3: repeated timeouts at ~5.0 s; connect/starttransfer times 0 → indicates no established TCP session despite IP reachability.\n  - ICMP to same endpoints succeeds, confirming selective failure for TCP port 80 only.\n\n5) Service listening state in server farm\n- load_balancer: netstat shows TCP 0.0.0.0:80 LISTEN\n- web_server_0: TCP 0.0.0.0:80 LISTEN\n- No host- or router-side packet filters observed on these servers/routers that would block HTTP.\n\n6) Host-local firewall rules\n- host_2_1_1_1 nftables ruleset:\n  - table inet filter:\n    - chain output: policy accept; rule: tcp dport 80 drop\n    - chain input: tcp dport 80 drop\n    - chain forward: tcp dport 80 drop\n- host_1_1_1_1: no such drop rules (nft ruleset not present; default ACCEPT).\n\nAssessment of Network Health\n- Core/distribution/server routing and IP reachability: Healthy (OSPF and L3 forwarding working).\n- DNS: Healthy (resolution successful from both hosts).\n- Server farm services: Listening on TCP/80 and reachable from at least one host (host_1_1_1_1).\n- End-to-end HTTP from host_1_1_1_1: Normal.\n- End-to-end HTTP from host_2_1_1_1: Abnormal (consistent failures/timeouts specific to TCP/80).\n\nAnomaly Detected\n- host_2_1_1_1 cannot establish HTTP (TCP/80) sessions to any server (LB or web servers), despite normal ICMP reachability and correct routing/DNS.\n\nLocalization of Faulty Device\n- Fault localized to host_2_1_1_1 itself (endpoint).\n  - Evidence: nftables rule on host_2_1_1_1 explicitly drops tcp dport 80 in output chain, which will block all outbound HTTP connections from this host.\n\nRoot Cause\n- Misconfigured local firewall (nftables) on host_2_1_1_1 dropping TCP destination port 80 in the output chain, causing HTTP connection attempts to time out.\n\nImpact\n- host_2_1_1_1 is unable to access any HTTP-based services in the environment, including the load balancer and web servers, while other hosts (e.g., host_1_1_1_1) can access them normally.\n- Network infrastructure (routers/switches/server farm) appears unaffected; the issue is isolated to the single endpoint’s local firewall configuration.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 19019, "output_tokens": 3779, "total_tokens": 22798, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 18048}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2560}}}
